				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=11366"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=11249"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Unless you are building far too many military bases and/or gunboats.  Then you could actually be easily attacked and if those gunboats are all in the ship pool, you could be killed outright by that player making the big PP.<br />
<br />
*EDIT*<br />
<br />
Actually, the number of bases (factories or labs) doesn't figure into the power given to you by the planets from what I can tell.  The power you get from planets comes from the planet (some base value) plus the population.  You also recieve power based on the technologies you have developed, and the rest comes from ships that you own (fleeted or not).  So if your planets have a bunch of military bases and not enough factories you will be producing very little PP, while you might have a high &quot;power&quot; level because of the other things mentioned.<br />
<br />
I think that every 100k population gives you one point of power.  Keep in mind that bases/factories/labs only produce if there is enough population to man them.			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
